# Enforce LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# Rationale (audit, 2026-06): with core.autocrlf=true and no .gitattributes,
# git checked out the LF-committed IR schema as CRLF on Windows. The Rust
# emitter writes LF, so `committed_schema_matches_fresh_emit` (Gate 1
# determinism acceptance) went RED on Windows-local while staying green on
# the Linux-only CI -- a gate whose colour depended on the developer's OS.
# Pinning eol=lf makes byte-exact / hash / schema-determinism checks
# platform-independent, which the spec's determinism guarantees require.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Content-addressed canonical artifacts are binary; never line-ending-normalize
# them (they already contain NUL bytes, but be explicit so the hash contract is
# never at the mercy of attribute inference).
*.bin binary

# Shell scripts must stay LF regardless of inference (they run under Git Bash
# on Windows and bash in CI).
*.sh text eol=lf
